TASK 1

In Option A, I chose five bookmakers to check if over/under 2.5 game result can be explained by the odds for different types of bets. In order to do that, I was asked to choose a unsupervised way unlike regression. Hence, I performed Principal Component Analysis (PCA) and reduce the dimension of my feature vector. Creating a feature vector that can give me the oppurtunity to see if over/under 2.5 game result can be explained by the odds for different types of bets is the primary issue. Firstly, I filtered my odd details data with total handicap that equals to 2.5 and certain bookmaker. By means of this, I obtain a matrix of over 2.5 and under odds 2.5 for a bookmaker. Afterwards, I just filtered that bookmaker to see the other odd types and related odds of that bookmaker. Later, I merged these two matrices and use it as my feature vector. Finally I did PCA with this vector and plot it. After plotting, I comment on the plots and eigenvector, variance covered etc. for five bookmakers.

In Option B, I used the same feature vector in order to do Multidimensional Scaling (MDS) for both “Euclidean” and “Manhattan” types of distances seperately. I plotted them and investigate if there is any difference between these two plots.

PCA helps dimensional reduction by coverting feature vector’s variables into scalars of principle component’s scores. FOR BET365

Bet365_over_under_final=odds_ov_un_final[bookmaker==‘bet365’] Bet365_wide_final=dcast(Bet365_over_under_final,matchId~oddtype,value.var=‘final_odd’)

odds[ ,match_date := anydate(date)] odds_oddtype=odds[order(matchId, oddtype,bookmaker,date)] odds_oddtype_final=odds[,list(final_odd=odd[.N]),by=list(matchId,oddtype,bookmaker)] Bet365_oddtype=odds_oddtype_final[bookmaker==‘bet365’] Bet365_wide_oddtype=dcast(Bet365_oddtype,matchId~oddtype,value.var=‘final_odd’) Bet365_wide_oddtype[,over:=NULL] Bet365_wide_oddtype[,under:=NULL]

merged_odds_Bet365=merge(Bet365_wide_final,Bet365_wide_oddtype,by=‘matchId’) merged_odds_Bet365_complete=merged_odds_Bet365[complete.cases(merged_odds_Bet365)]

PCA_Bet365<-princomp(merged_odds_Bet365_complete[,2:13], cor=T) merged_odds_Bet365_combined<-cbind(merged_odds_Bet365,PCA_Bet365$scores[,1:2]) matches=unique(matches) matches=matches[complete.cases(matches)] matches[ ,match_date := anydate(date)] matches[ ,match_time := anytime(date)] matches[,c(“HomeGoals”,“AwayGoals”):=tstrsplit(score,‘:’)] matches[,HomeGoals:=as.numeric(HomeGoals)] matches[,AwayGoals:=as.numeric(AwayGoals)] matches[,TotalGoals:=HomeGoals+AwayGoals] matches[,OverUnder:=0] matches[TotalGoals>2.5,OverUnder:=1] merged_odds_Bet365_forplot=merge(merged_odds_Bet365,matches,by=‘matchId’) matrix_pca_forplot_matchId<-merged_odds_Bet365_forplot[,-14:-24] matrix_pca_forplot_matchId<-matrix_pca_forplot_matchId[,-2:-13]

merged_odds_Bet365_combined_OverUnder<-merge( merged_odds_Bet365_combined,matrix_pca_forplot_matchId, by=‘matchId’ )

ggplot(merged_odds_Bet365_combined_OverUnder,aes( Comp.1, Comp.2,col=OverUnder,fill=OverUnder))+stat_ellipse(geom=“polygon”,col=“black”,alpha=0.5)+geom_point(shape=21,col=“blue”)

FOR BET365

dist_Bet365<-dist(t(merged_odds_Bet365[,2:13]),method = “euclidean”) mds_Bet365<-cmdscale(dist_Bet365,eig = TRUE,x.ret = TRUE) mds.var<-round(mds_Bet365\(eig/sum(mds_Bet365\)eig)*100,1) mds.values.Bet365<-mds_Bet365$points mds.data.Bet365<-data.frame(sample=rownames(mds.values.Bet365), X=mds.values.Bet365[,1], Y=mds.values.Bet365[,2]) ggplot(data=mds.data.Bet365, aes(x=X, y=Y, label=sample)) + geom_text() + theme_bw() + xlab(paste(“MDS1 -”, mds.var[1], “%”, sep="“)) + ylab(paste(”MDS2 - “, mds.var[2],”%“, sep=”“)) + ggtitle(”MDS Plot Using Euclidean Distance for Bet365")

dist_Bet365<-dist(t(merged_odds_Bet365[,2:13]),method = “manhattan”) mds_Bet365<-cmdscale(dist_Bet365,eig = TRUE,x.ret = TRUE) mds.var<-round(mds_Bet365\(eig/sum(mds_Bet365\)eig)*100,1) mds.values.Bet365<-mds_Bet365$points mds.data.Bet365<-data.frame(sample=rownames(mds.values.Bet365), X=mds.values.Bet365[,1], Y=mds.values.Bet365[,2]) ggplot(data=mds.data.Bet365, aes(x=X, y=Y, label=sample)) + geom_text() + theme_bw() + xlab(paste(“MDS1 -”, mds.var[1], “%”, sep="“)) + ylab(paste(”MDS2 - “, mds.var[2],”%“, sep=”“)) + ggtitle(”MDS Plot Using Manhattan Distance for Bet365")
